    "role": "MCP tool collection exposing ArchSpine's introspection, scanning, drift detection, and dependency graph capabilities as callable MCP tools for LLM agent integration.",
    "responsibilities": [
      "Provide MCP tool definitions and handlers for all ArchSpine core features.",
      "Expose methods to query project baseline and sync status.",
      "Enable querying of architectural invariants and responsibilities from rules and spine units.",
      "Facilitate symbol search across the indexed project symbols.",
      "Support preview scans without persisting results.",
      "Retrieve drift history for symbols or modules.",
      "Provide file context, view data, and violation summaries.",
      "List available MCP resource templates.",
      "Offer dependency graph queries (upstream, downstream, violation edges) and diagnostics (cycles, dead code).",
      "Perform semantic matching and change impact analysis on the dependency graph.",
      "Compute semantic diffs between states."
